        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 3:44PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM EDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
line of strong thunderstorms along a line extending from 6 miles
southeast of Toomsboro to 6 miles north of Danville, and moving
east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail, frequent cloud to ground
lightning and increased chance of a brief tornado.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...While winds should result in minor damage to tree limbs and
blowing around of light, unsecured objects, the leading
edge of this line of storms has also exhibited areas of
localized rotation. A brief tornado could quickly form.

Locations impacted include...
Wrightsville, Chappells Mill, Lovett, Spann, Nicklesville, and
Tuckers Crossroad.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
central and east central Georgia.</instruction>
